WEBVTT

00:04.874 --> 00:07.137
[old time piano music]
♪♪

00:13.970 --> 00:16.407
[distant floor sweeping]

00:24.937 --> 00:26.983
[old time music continues]
♪♪

00:55.968 --> 00:58.449
[intense electronic music]
♪♪

01:10.809 --> 01:13.073
[old time piano music]
♪♪

02:01.033 --> 02:03.123
[wind howling]

02:08.345 --> 02:09.781
- Hey beautiful.
- Hi.

02:10.217 --> 02:11.435
- I just gotta run
to the store real fast,

02:11.479 --> 02:13.045
case we get snowed in.

02:13.089 --> 02:14.264
- 'Kay.

02:16.571 --> 02:17.746
- How was school?

02:17.789 --> 02:19.269
- Fine.

02:19.313 --> 02:21.837
Miss Nichols says I can't
wear dark lipstick anymore.

02:22.490 --> 02:24.753
- You want me to go in
and kick her ass?

02:27.495 --> 02:29.932
- Are we going hunting
this weekend?
- Mm-hmm.

02:31.325 --> 02:32.761
- Remember,

02:32.804 --> 02:34.937
I'm gonna get my seventh
in under twenty.

02:35.329 --> 02:37.157
- I don't doubt it.

02:44.207 --> 02:45.861
- Wanna go sledding tonight?

02:45.904 --> 02:47.297
- Sure.

02:47.341 --> 02:50.518
Oh, wait, I got a session
with Mrs. Minskey tonight.

02:51.301 --> 02:53.738
- She still tryin' to talk
to her dead husband?

02:53.782 --> 02:56.088
- Yeah, but I'm gonna shake her
out of a little more money

02:56.132 --> 02:58.439
before she gets
to talk to him.

02:58.482 --> 03:01.006
- That's cunty.
I like it.

03:01.050 --> 03:02.051
[chuckles lightly]
- Thank you.

03:02.094 --> 03:03.618
That's called business.

03:03.661 --> 03:04.967
- Noted.

03:12.714 --> 03:14.846
[V/O on radio]
- All righty now, W.H.E.L.
mountain radio,

03:14.890 --> 03:17.588
it's 7:16
and it's cold out there.

03:17.632 --> 03:20.852
Sub-zero temperature gonna be all night long with wind chill--

03:20.896 --> 03:22.854
- What's goin' on, man?
That's it?

03:22.898 --> 03:24.334
[V/O on radio]
- Stay safe out there folks,

03:24.378 --> 03:25.727
this storm is one
for the record books--

03:25.770 --> 03:26.771
- Twelve fifty.

03:27.642 --> 03:28.991
- Stockin' up for the storm?

03:29.034 --> 03:30.297
[V/O] on radio]
- Stay off the road,

03:30.340 --> 03:31.820
and let the road cleaners
do their work.

03:32.647 --> 03:34.126
- Drive safe out there.

03:34.779 --> 03:36.041
- Mom, I'm gonna get
a cinnamon

03:36.085 --> 03:37.652
coffee cake cappuccino.

03:37.695 --> 03:39.001
[door bell dings]
You want one?

03:39.044 --> 03:40.872
- No, and you can't
have one either.

03:40.916 --> 03:41.960
- Why?

03:42.004 --> 03:43.135
- Because you'll be
up all night.

03:43.484 --> 03:45.094
- Good, I'm gonna be
sledding all night.

03:45.137 --> 03:47.139
- No, I can't be at the bottom
of the road to watch you.

03:47.183 --> 03:49.185
I got that session
with Mrs. Minskey.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.926
And I know
you have homework.

03:52.014 --> 03:53.885
- Fuck homework.

03:56.845 --> 03:59.021
[wind howling]

04:06.420 --> 04:08.465
[car engine starting]

04:12.991 --> 04:14.645
[Echo grunts in effort]

04:16.038 --> 04:18.083
[Ivy laughs]
- Ah!
- Ah!

04:20.260 --> 04:22.436
[wind howling]

04:35.623 --> 04:37.625
[Kurt chews food]

04:45.285 --> 04:46.982
- So, how we doin'
over here?

04:48.897 --> 04:50.899
- Lemme get another shot
and a beer.

04:55.860 --> 04:58.123
[chews food]

05:07.219 --> 05:09.091
- What are we asking
of the cards tonight,

05:09.134 --> 05:10.962
Mrs. Minskey?

05:11.006 --> 05:14.226
- I'd like to know if my
sciatica will ever go away.

05:14.270 --> 05:15.532
It hurts!

05:16.664 --> 05:17.882
[card snaps]

05:17.926 --> 05:19.362
Also,

05:19.406 --> 05:22.278
I'd like to know if my son
is ever going to visit me.

05:22.800 --> 05:24.541
Maybe a phone call.

05:25.586 --> 05:26.848
[card snaps]

05:27.544 --> 05:29.503
But most of all,

05:29.546 --> 05:33.158
I'd like to speak
to my beloved husband.

05:33.463 --> 05:35.465
My darling Ivan.

05:35.509 --> 05:37.075
Can we do that, please?

05:37.119 --> 05:38.773
[card snaps]

05:39.991 --> 05:42.124
Is that a good one
or a bad one?

05:42.167 --> 05:44.344
[breathes in deeply]

05:44.909 --> 05:47.564
- Whispers from the shadows.

05:48.260 --> 05:49.914
Pass through the filament

05:49.958 --> 05:52.482
and pierce this
earthly realm.

05:53.570 --> 05:58.009
Two hearts, once one,
still yearn to shine.

05:58.880 --> 06:02.274
Bound by love,
locked in time.

06:02.623 --> 06:05.626
Listen now
and hear our calls.

06:05.669 --> 06:09.194
Show a sign
within these walls.

06:09.325 --> 06:10.631
Ivan.

06:11.588 --> 06:13.111
Ivan Minskey?

06:13.982 --> 06:15.766
Are you there, Ivan?

06:17.202 --> 06:18.987
Can you hear us?

06:20.292 --> 06:22.077
- Ivan, honey, I'm here.

06:22.904 --> 06:24.427
I'm here.

06:25.472 --> 06:28.431
Please, please
won't you talk to us?

06:29.998 --> 06:33.175
[sighs]
- The filament is thick.

06:33.218 --> 06:35.830
The veil won't part.

06:46.362 --> 06:48.538
Oh, Valley of Death.

06:48.582 --> 06:51.585
We stand on the
Mountain of Hope.

06:51.976 --> 06:53.761
We call out your name,

06:53.804 --> 06:57.286
but all we hear
is an echo.

06:59.070 --> 07:00.855
[V/O whispers]
- Mom.

07:00.898 --> 07:02.596
I'm sorry.

07:03.553 --> 07:04.989
[softly]
I love you.

07:05.033 --> 07:06.948
- A whisper?

07:10.125 --> 07:11.779
No.

07:13.215 --> 07:14.912
[exhales]
No.

07:16.784 --> 07:18.916
Nothing.

07:19.308 --> 07:20.483
- Oh well.

07:21.092 --> 07:23.225
We'll try again next time.

07:33.801 --> 07:36.630
[woman singing old song]
♪ I remember you

07:37.587 --> 07:40.764
♪ I remember you

07:41.461 --> 07:44.725
♪ A woman true to fella
with the open umbrella

07:44.768 --> 07:48.859
♪ That I met one rainy day
upon the avenue

07:48.903 --> 07:52.254
♪ I remember you

07:52.297 --> 07:54.082
[music stops]

08:06.747 --> 08:08.749
[door squeaks open]

08:09.576 --> 08:11.795
[wind whistling]

08:24.199 --> 08:26.593
[car engine humming]

08:41.433 --> 08:43.217
[thud]

09:22.518 --> 09:23.345
[softly]
- No.

09:23.388 --> 09:25.652
[breathes heavily]
No. No.

09:35.792 --> 09:37.446
[sniffles]

09:44.671 --> 09:46.498
[car engine revs]

10:19.880 --> 10:21.490
[Kurt sighs]

10:22.404 --> 10:23.927
[whispers]
My God.

10:26.364 --> 10:28.366
[Kurt breathes heavily]

10:35.722 --> 10:38.028
[panting]

10:38.725 --> 10:40.422
[grunts in effort]

10:46.384 --> 10:48.604
[panting]

10:59.180 --> 11:01.312
[car engine revs]

11:08.755 --> 11:11.279
[groans]
[breathes heavily]

11:12.454 --> 11:14.804
[windshield wipers squeaking]

11:39.307 --> 11:41.657
[shovel clinks]
[grunts in effort]

11:46.575 --> 11:49.012
[wind howling]

12:15.996 --> 12:18.172
[breathes shakily]

12:27.094 --> 12:29.487
[breathes heavily]

12:38.322 --> 12:39.846
[coughs]
[spits]

12:42.544 --> 12:44.764
[breathes heavily]
Ha! Ha.

12:48.202 --> 12:49.507
[softly]
- Wait.

12:50.552 --> 12:51.858
[softly]
Stop.

12:53.337 --> 12:55.339
[Kurt breathes heavily]
[kicking in bathtub]

12:56.645 --> 12:58.560
[Echo whimpers]

12:59.909 --> 13:02.172
[muffled moans]

13:04.522 --> 13:07.177
[ominous music builds]
♪♪

13:15.882 --> 13:18.145
[Kurt breathes heavily]

13:39.906 --> 13:42.560
[Ivy on phone]
- I need to report
a missing person, please.

13:45.912 --> 13:48.044
Echo Allen,
she's my daughter.

13:49.654 --> 13:51.265
She's fourteen.

13:53.876 --> 13:55.965
Uh, seven o'clock.

14:00.361 --> 14:02.450
I came home from work
about fifteen minutes ago,

14:02.493 --> 14:04.800
and she wasn't here.

14:04.844 --> 14:06.802
She's not here.

14:09.979 --> 14:13.504
Yeah, yeah, I'm sure
that she's not here.

14:13.548 --> 14:16.986
Her coat is gone
and her sled is gone,

14:17.030 --> 14:20.120
but if she went sledding,
she didn't come back.

14:21.686 --> 14:24.124
[echoing]
No, no she couldn't
be out there,

14:24.167 --> 14:26.909
I just drove up my road,
I would've seen her.

14:29.999 --> 14:32.349
[echoing]
Fifteen Old Bark Road.

14:32.393 --> 14:34.874
One five Bark Road.

14:36.658 --> 14:39.008
[wind howling]

15:45.422 --> 15:47.859
[static on radio]

15:52.429 --> 15:53.822
- [V/O on radio] Norm Daniels
here with the weather.

15:53.865 --> 15:57.130
Snow, snow,
and more snow, folks.

15:57.173 --> 15:59.349
It's already cold.

16:00.307 --> 16:02.091
Risin' temps by noon.

16:02.135 --> 16:04.050
High in the teens
and sunny all day

16:04.093 --> 16:06.008
with a chance of rain
late Tuesday

16:06.052 --> 16:08.445
when it all turns to slush,
folks.

16:08.489 --> 16:09.620
That's the weather.

16:09.664 --> 16:12.058
That's the way
the cookie crumbles.

16:12.101 --> 16:13.059
Stay tuned for--

16:30.163 --> 16:31.686
- Echo!

16:36.386 --> 16:38.345
Echo!

16:49.530 --> 16:51.880
[bar crowd chatter]

17:16.731 --> 17:18.993
[wind whistling]

17:39.406 --> 17:41.147
[car door thuds]

17:53.811 --> 17:55.422
[Kurt exhales]

18:12.961 --> 18:15.050
[knocking on door]

18:20.882 --> 18:22.971
[knocking continues]

18:25.930 --> 18:27.367
- Hold it.

18:29.020 --> 18:30.326
- Hey.
- Hey.

18:30.370 --> 18:33.590
- Uh, hey, can uh,
we talk to you for a second?

18:34.113 --> 18:35.505
- Yeah.

18:35.549 --> 18:37.333
Go round, I could ta--
[exhales]

18:37.377 --> 18:39.683
talk to you over here,
I can't get this door open.

18:39.727 --> 18:41.598
- 'Kay.
- All right.

18:49.258 --> 18:51.042
- I'm Detective Jay Sanford,

18:51.086 --> 18:52.435
this is Detective Davide.

18:52.479 --> 18:54.481
We're with the Sullivan
County Police Department.

18:54.524 --> 18:55.960
- Good morning.
- Hi.

18:56.004 --> 18:58.180
- Hey, uh, we're lookin'
for your neighbor's daughter.

18:58.224 --> 18:59.312
Fourteen year old girl?

18:59.355 --> 19:01.183
She's been missing
since last night.

19:01.227 --> 19:03.359
Have you happened
to see her at all?
- No. No.

19:03.403 --> 19:05.927
- Do you know your uh,
neighbors down the road?

19:05.970 --> 19:07.233
- I don't.

19:08.103 --> 19:09.670
- Echo Allen.

19:09.713 --> 19:11.324
Ring any bells?

19:11.715 --> 19:13.282
- No.

19:13.891 --> 19:15.676
- Not familiar at all?

19:17.373 --> 19:19.288
- No.

19:19.767 --> 19:20.811
- What's your name?

19:20.855 --> 19:22.117
- Kurt Miller.

19:22.770 --> 19:24.511
- Were ya out
and about it all last night?

19:24.554 --> 19:26.861
- Uh, went to Main Street
and had dinner.

19:26.904 --> 19:27.949
Couple drinks.

19:27.992 --> 19:29.342
- What time you stay 'til?
- Late.

19:29.385 --> 19:30.473
- How late?

19:30.517 --> 19:31.648
- I-- I wasn't
keeping track of time,

19:31.692 --> 19:33.955
but probably I left
around ten?

19:33.998 --> 19:35.565
- That's not that late.

19:35.609 --> 19:37.872
Did you see anybody
on the road?

19:37.915 --> 19:39.090
- No.

19:39.787 --> 19:41.484
- Not even a deer?

19:43.138 --> 19:45.271
- Maybe, I don't know.
I...

19:46.663 --> 19:48.796
- You okay?
Look a little nervous.

19:50.493 --> 19:52.408
- Nah, no.

19:53.322 --> 19:54.628
Just tired.

19:54.671 --> 19:56.195
- Okay.

19:58.501 --> 19:59.981
If you happen to
think of anything,

20:00.024 --> 20:01.983
you happen to see her,
if you would,

20:02.026 --> 20:03.941
please give us a phone call.

20:03.985 --> 20:05.291
- All right,
you have a nice day.

20:05.334 --> 20:06.161
- You too.

20:06.205 --> 20:07.858
- All right, thanks.

20:22.090 --> 20:24.266
[distant radio static]

20:28.357 --> 20:31.621
♪ Ev'ry morning,
ev'ry evening

20:31.665 --> 20:33.536
♪ Ain't we got fun?

20:33.580 --> 20:34.885
[static/buzzing on radio]

20:34.929 --> 20:37.758
♪ Not much money,
oh, but honey

20:37.801 --> 20:39.760
♪ Ain't we got fun?

20:40.717 --> 20:42.719
♪ The rent's unpaid, dear

20:42.763 --> 20:44.330
[radio clicks off]

20:47.158 --> 20:49.596
[footsteps leaving]

20:55.384 --> 20:58.039
[ominous music pulsing]
♪♪

21:08.223 --> 21:10.051
[tape ripping]

21:32.639 --> 21:34.728
[scanner whirring]

21:55.488 --> 21:58.404
[rain pouring down]

21:59.187 --> 22:01.581
[Kurt breathing heavily]

22:02.408 --> 22:05.193
[ominous music pulsing]
♪♪

22:13.288 --> 22:15.725
[V/O on radio]
- All righty now.
This is ninety-two W.H.E.L.

22:15.769 --> 22:17.901
with your host Frankie Wood
rockin' the mountain.

22:17.945 --> 22:20.208
More rain expected today
through the afternoon,

22:20.251 --> 22:22.297
which should be heavy
at times.

22:22.341 --> 22:24.125
Nights...

22:24.168 --> 22:26.693
[radio static]
♪ In the winter,
in the summer

22:29.217 --> 22:30.305
[V/O on radio]
Gimme a call,

22:30.349 --> 22:31.262
maybe I'll play
something for ya.

22:31.306 --> 22:32.655
[rock music playing]
♪♪

22:42.535 --> 22:43.927
- Yeah, I'll be right there,
bro.

22:44.711 --> 22:46.365
Just gimme a sec.

22:49.890 --> 22:51.674
[door bell jingles]

22:55.765 --> 22:57.071
Hey.

22:57.114 --> 22:58.507
- Hey, can you make
sure that everyone

22:58.551 --> 23:00.204
who comes in here
takes one of these?

23:04.600 --> 23:06.254
[door bell jingles]

23:08.082 --> 23:09.953
- Hey, what's up, man?
How you doin'?

23:09.997 --> 23:11.520
All set?

23:12.303 --> 23:13.914
That's it?
- Yeah.

23:17.657 --> 23:19.223
- Fifteen.

23:21.225 --> 23:23.097
- Need a bag by any chance?
- No.

23:26.970 --> 23:28.015
- Hey man,
before you leave,

23:28.058 --> 23:29.712
you wanna spread the word?

23:29.756 --> 23:31.540
She's a good kid.

23:33.020 --> 23:34.500
[register drawer shuts]

23:58.785 --> 24:00.526
[car engine revs]

25:01.500 --> 25:04.111
[exhales]
[breathes heavily]

25:12.641 --> 25:14.469
[grunts in effort]

25:38.319 --> 25:40.016
[grunts]

25:40.060 --> 25:42.671
[breathes heavily]

25:46.109 --> 25:48.895
[car passing by]

25:52.420 --> 25:53.856
[grunts in effort]

26:13.659 --> 26:15.878
[breathes heavily]

26:45.038 --> 26:47.083
[drill whirring]

26:52.698 --> 26:54.830
[grunts in effort]

27:04.884 --> 27:06.886
[exhales]

27:10.106 --> 27:12.543
[distant bang]

27:40.659 --> 27:41.921
- Hello?

27:44.227 --> 27:45.228
Hello?

27:45.272 --> 27:46.665
- Yeah, hold on.

27:47.056 --> 27:49.102
- Oh hey, um,
could uh--

27:49.145 --> 27:51.017
could I just talk to you
for a second?

27:51.060 --> 27:53.976
I'm Ivy Allen, I--
I live down the road um,

27:54.020 --> 27:56.326
I'm lookin' for
my daughter, Echo?

27:57.458 --> 27:59.112
You know her?

28:03.029 --> 28:06.206
[sighs]
We live right down the road.

28:06.249 --> 28:08.338
She rides her bike here.
Are you sure?

28:10.993 --> 28:13.474
- Yeah, I don't know her,
I've never seen her.

28:16.912 --> 28:18.348
- Did the cops come?

28:19.175 --> 28:20.481
- Yeah.

28:20.524 --> 28:22.352
- She didn't run away.

28:28.271 --> 28:30.709
So you're tryin' to
resurrect this dump?

28:31.361 --> 28:32.232
- Yeah.

28:32.275 --> 28:34.147
I'm gonna fix it
and flip it.

28:35.931 --> 28:37.019
- It's been abandoned
for years.

28:37.063 --> 28:39.021
We used to come here
to party.

28:40.109 --> 28:42.895
You must've cleaned out
a lot of glass and beer cans.

28:45.680 --> 28:47.377
What's your name?

28:48.030 --> 28:49.684
[distant bangs]
- Kurt.

28:52.339 --> 28:53.775
- You got a cat?

28:53.819 --> 28:58.040
- No this house just...
makes noise.

28:59.041 --> 29:00.739
[loudly]
- Echo!

29:09.356 --> 29:10.792
I saw you on the road
the other day,

29:10.836 --> 29:12.228
you didn't stop.

29:13.534 --> 29:14.970
- Huh,
I don't remember that.

29:15.014 --> 29:16.885
- Yeah,
then I saw you in the town.

29:18.060 --> 29:20.062
- I doubt that was me.

29:20.106 --> 29:22.673
- It was you.
It's okay.

29:23.979 --> 29:26.765
[sighs]
Well, I live--

29:29.376 --> 29:31.682
We live in the first house
this side of the cemetery,

29:31.726 --> 29:33.641
up the steep drive?

29:33.684 --> 29:35.121
Okay?

29:53.313 --> 29:55.228
[Echo whispers]
- I love you.

30:13.376 --> 30:15.552
[thunder rumbling]

31:02.948 --> 31:05.428
[eerie music whirring]
♪♪

31:26.667 --> 31:28.277
[whispers]
- Four, five, six, seven.

31:28.321 --> 31:29.931
[gasps]

31:33.979 --> 31:35.719
[whispers]
Seven circles.

31:35.763 --> 31:38.157
[eerie music]
♪♪

31:47.514 --> 31:49.168
[distant thud]

31:52.911 --> 31:55.348
[distant creaking]

32:04.879 --> 32:06.663
[door creaks]

32:17.239 --> 32:19.415
[distant knocking]

32:20.590 --> 32:22.941
[Kurt breathes heavily]

32:38.347 --> 32:41.220
[distant radio playing]

32:43.657 --> 32:46.747
♪ Ev'ry morning,
ev'ry evening

32:46.790 --> 32:48.792
♪ Ain't we got fun?

32:49.750 --> 32:52.971
[radio static]
♪ Not much money,
oh, but honey

32:53.014 --> 32:54.929
♪ Ain't we got fun?

32:56.235 --> 32:59.107
[radio static]
♪ The rent's unpaid, dear

32:59.151 --> 33:01.370
♪ We haven't a bus

33:02.981 --> 33:04.983
[radio stations changing]

33:05.548 --> 33:07.768
♪ For people like us

33:08.334 --> 33:10.075
♪ In the winter,
in the summer

33:10.118 --> 33:12.207
[pounding on radio]
[radio stops]

33:18.083 --> 33:19.867
[radio static]

33:23.131 --> 33:25.481
♪ Don't we have fun?

33:41.106 --> 33:42.411
- All right.

33:43.369 --> 33:45.284
You wanna fuck with me?

34:02.692 --> 34:04.520
[rifle clicking]

34:08.742 --> 34:11.005
[rifle cocks]

34:17.793 --> 34:19.447
[ghostly whispers]
- I see.

34:20.014 --> 34:21.668
[eerie music pulsing]
♪♪

34:42.558 --> 34:44.473
[distant door creaking]

34:45.431 --> 34:47.302
[distant whistle]

34:54.918 --> 34:57.094
[door creaks]

35:29.039 --> 35:30.780
[ghostly whispers]
Down here.

